---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import { SITE } from '../consts';
const updated = '2026-04-18';
---
<Layout title="Privacy Policy" description={`How ${SITE.name} handles (and does not handle) your data.`}>
  <article class="container-prose py-20 prose dark:prose-invert">
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p><em>Last updated: {updated}</em></p>
    <p>
      {SITE.name} ("we", "our", or "the app") is an Android launcher built with privacy as a core
      principle. This Privacy Policy explains, in plain language, what information the app does and
      does not handle. It applies to the {SITE.name} application distributed on Google Play under
      the package name <code>{SITE.packageName}</code> and to this website.
    </p>

    <h2>Summary</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>We do not collect, transmit, or sell personal data.</li>
      <li>The app contains no advertising or analytics SDKs.</li>
      <li>All data the app reads (installed apps, contacts if you grant access, usage counts) stays on your device.</li>
      <li>The app works offline and does not require an account.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Information processed locally on your device</h2>
    <p>To function as a launcher, {SITE.name} reads the following information from your device. None of it leaves your device.</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Installed applications.</strong> Names, icons, and package identifiers, so you can search and launch them.</li>
      <li><strong>App launch counts and recency</strong> (optional), used to order search results by relevance. Stored in the app's private storage and deleted when you uninstall.</li>
      <li><strong>Contacts</strong> (optional, permission-gated). Used only to make contacts searchable from the launcher. Never transmitted.</li>
      <li><strong>Shortcuts and user preferences.</strong> Pinned apps, tags, themes, and settings are stored in Android's local <code>SharedPreferences</code>.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Permissions we request and why</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>QUERY_ALL_PACKAGES / GET_PACKAGES</strong> — to display and launch your installed apps.</li>
      <li><strong>READ_CONTACTS</strong> (optional) — to search contacts from the launcher. Revocable from Android Settings.</li>
      <li><strong>CALL_PHONE</strong> (optional) — to place a call directly from a contact result.</li>
      <li><strong>EXPAND_STATUS_BAR</strong> — to toggle the notification shade via gesture.</li>
      <li><strong>Accessibility service</strong> (optional) — only if you enable gesture locking; it performs the lock action and reads nothing.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>We do not request <strong>INTERNET</strong>. The app cannot make network calls.</p>

    <h2>Data we do not collect</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>No personal identifiers, email, phone number, or account.</li>
      <li>No device identifiers, advertising IDs, or IP addresses.</li>
      <li>No location data, photos, files, SMS, or call logs.</li>
      <li>No crash reports or diagnostic telemetry.</li>
      <li>No cookies or trackers in the app.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Third parties</h2>
    <p>
      {SITE.name} integrates with no third-party services, advertising networks, analytics
      providers, or cloud backends. Google Play itself may collect installation and crash data at
      the platform level; that data is governed by Google's privacy policy, not ours.
    </p>

    <h2>Children</h2>
    <p>
      {SITE.name} is not directed to children under 13. Because we do not collect any personal
      information from any user, we do not collect any from children either.
    </p>

    <h2>Your rights</h2>
    <p>
      Because no data leaves your device, there is nothing for us to export or erase on your behalf.
      You can remove all app data at any time by uninstalling the app or clearing its storage from
      Android Settings → Apps → {SITE.name} → Storage → Clear data. See also
      <a href="/account-deletion">Account &amp; Data Deletion</a>.
    </p>

    <h2>Security</h2>
    <p>
      All data remains in Android's app-private sandbox. We recommend enabling device encryption
      and a screen lock, which Android provides at the OS level.
    </p>

    <h2>Changes</h2>
    <p>
      If this policy changes, the "Last updated" date above will change. Material changes will be
      announced on the blog and in release notes. Continued use of the app after an update
      constitutes acceptance of the revised policy.
    </p>

    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>
      Questions or concerns? Email
      <a href={`mailto:${SITE.email}`}>{SITE.email}</a>. We are a small, independent project and
      will respond within a reasonable timeframe.
    </p>
  </article>
</Layout>
